 urged the court to admit the defendant to bail in most liberal term, adding that his client would not jump bail but provide reliable surety. Magistrate Joseph Owolawi admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N100,000 with one surety in like sum and adjourned the matter till June 4, 2020, for hearing. Vanguard News Nigeria. A 35-year-old man, Bawa Joshua, on Monday appeared in an Ado-Ekiti Chief Magistrates’ Court, for allegedly pouring hot semovita on his wife, Grace. May 14, 2018 In "Just Human" A 41- year-old housewife, Janet Ojukwu, was on Tuesday arraigned in Lagos for allegedly pouring hot water on her husband’s ex-wife’s face. Ojukwu, who resides at Makoko area of Yaba, Lagos, is facing a charge of assault occasioning harm before  a Yaba Magistrates’ Court.  She however, pleaded not guilty. The… November 26, 2019 In "Metro" A 35-year old woman, Esther Ariyo has been remanded by an Abeokuta Magistrate court sitting in Isabo for allegedly pouring hot water on one of her customers, Benson Anthony. August 15, 2018 In "Crime Alert"